{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0c4f997-4538-4386-b12b-f04525a781c9","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` but depends on it.\n\nFix: swap `Domain.fs` to come before `Services.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_3Ss90vqVPIYzxzZH13OJ4A","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7801b05f57304a2c88277197f1d8eaab/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7801b05f57304a2c88277197f1d8eaab/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"42af6ddf-4c91-41f1-bb89-2c03bb084fa1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order` type)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines `Order`, `OrderId`, `OrderItem`\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which hasn't been compiled yet. The fix is to put `Domain.fs` first.","outputTokens":401,"requestId":"5C0D:60C57:1DEB06D:21B967D:6A07C84E"},"id":"ef583416-8935-4cc4-9ca6-aef7e2659e29","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:54.134Z","parentId":"9893c6f3-9fd5-45c0-9962-1ccdfc5a6e64"}
